<dl id="n41191b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41191b">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41191b"> 191(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> c&apos;est vrai, lui / dit le roi</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&lsquo;Le roi Dagobert et le grand St &Eacute;loi&rsquo;: Le bon roi Dagobert / Avait sa culotte &agrave; l&apos;envers; / Le grand saint &Eacute;loi / Lui dit: &laquo;O mon roi! / Votre Majest&eacute; / Est mal culott&eacute;e. / &mdash; <mark>C&apos;est vrai, lui dit le roi</mark>, / Je vais la remettre &agrave; l&apos;endroit.&raquo; <font color="green">[Good King Dagobert / Had his breeches on inside out; / The great St Eloi / Said to him: O my king! Your Majesty / Is badly breeched. / That&apos;s true, the king said to him, / I&apos;m going to put them on the right side out.]</font> <small> V.-F. Verrimst, <a name="VFVR" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#VFVR"><cite title="source">Rondes et Chansons Populaires</cite></a> (1886) 161</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
